			<description><![CDATA[<p>What do five million documents, one hundred thousand clients and hundreds of colleges &amp; universities have in common? They&#39;re the marks of a very busy team. They&#39;re also some of the key metrics that drive Interfolio&#39;s business and we&#39;re looking for an operations specialist to help us grow by keeping our engines running flawlessly.&nbsp;</p><p>Interfolio works with colleges and universities to help them hire the best faculty and admit the best graduate students. Our vision is to be the leader in faculty recruitment and retention and to provide technology tools to reshape teaching and learning.</p><p>Our technology platform serves more than 140,000 students, faculty and administrators at over 1,700 schools each year. We are growing year-over-year and are looking for an Associate of Corporate Operations to join our team.</p><p>Interfolio was founded in 1999 in Washington, DC and remains headquartered downtown. We offer competitive salaries, great benefits and plenty of room for personal and professional growth.</p><p><strong>ROLE AND RESPONSIBILITIES</strong><br />The Associate of Corporate Operations and will work directly with the CEO on projects that impact every aspect of our business.&nbsp; You&#39;ll get experience and exposure that goes well beyond a typical associate-level position and you&#39;ll work on a wide range of projects with a proven, highly-experienced team of startup entrepreneurs.&nbsp; We&rsquo;re looking for someone to join our corporate operations team, contribute ideas, and pursue an amazing growth opportunity. If you want to roll up your sleeves and make things happen then Interfolio might be the opportunity you are looking for.&nbsp; In this position you&rsquo;ll be working closely with the CEO, the CFO, and the Strategy Team.</p><ul><li>You will work directly with the CEO, getting the opportunity to touch all pieces of the business including financial management, strategy, sales, marketing, administration and human resources.</li><li>You will have first line responsibility for accounting and human resources day-to-day matters, working directly with the CFO</li><li>You will be enthusiastically willing to roll up your sleeves and contribute in ways both large and small: from helping manage key business relationships, to processing accounts payable, to helping prepare for upcoming Board meetings.</li><li>You will build strong analytical models from raw data to produce a wide array of intelligence about financial forecasts, customer acquisition, pricing strategies, compensation analysis and other key priorities.</li><li>You will perform research on competitive landscape, prospective partnerships and new business opportunities</li><li>You will deliver on the full range of work required by a startup, including the small things, like opening and addressing the mail, managing office supplies or scheduling.</li><li>You will provide additional support to the CEO and other members of the leadership team as needed.</li></ul><p><strong>QUALIFICATIONS AND EDUCATION REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><ul style=""><li>You have a Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree or higher from a top school</li><li>You have at least 2 years of full time post-college work experience, ideally as an analyst/associate at a top-tier strategic consulting firm or investment bank</li><li>You have proven experience in financial modeling and analysis</li><li>You&rsquo;re a master at Excel and Powerpoint or Keynote</li></ul><p><br /><strong>PREFERRED SKILLS</strong></p><ul><li>You&rsquo;re highly organized, high energy, and a productive person -- you aim to achieve a lot in a day, and you generally do</li><li>You&rsquo;re highly resourceful &ndash; with a fanatical attention to detail</li><li>You have proven your ability to managing multiple, competing priorities</li><li>You understand and embrace the advantages and disadvantages of working in a startup &ndash; you&rsquo;re willing to take on any challenge</li><li>You understand a wide range of Internet-based products and services and use them to deliver great work</li><li>You have excellent interpersonal, communication and written skills, and a high level of maturity</li><li>Self-motivated and a self-starter is a must!</li></ul><p><strong>COMPENSATION PACKAGE</strong><br />Interfolio, Inc. offers a solid compensation package and benefits.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Interfolio, Inc. provides equal employment opportunities (EEO) to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, sexual orientation, national origin, age, disability, genetic information, marital status, amnesty, or status as a covered veteran in accordance with applicable federal, state and local laws. Interfolio, Inc. complies with applicable state and local laws governing non-discrimination in employment in every location in which the company has facilities.</p>]]></description>
